<doc>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR">
    <summary>
      <para>The
<b>DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR</b></para>
      <para>structure is one of the query result structures returned from an
<a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/api/winioctl/ni-winioctl-ioctl_storage_query_property">IOCTL_STORAGE_QUERY_PROPERTY</a> request. This
structure contains the copy offload capabilities for a storage device.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This structure is returned from a
<a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/api/winioctl/ni-winioctl-ioctl_storage_query_property">IOCTL_STORAGE_QUERY_PROPERTY</a> request when the
<b>PropertyId</b> member of
<see cref="STORAGE_PROPERTY_QUERY" /> is set to
<b>StorageDeviceCopyOffloadProperty</b>.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/FileIO/disk-management-structures">Disk Management Structures</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/api/winioctl/ni-winioctl-ioctl_storage_query_property">IOCTL_STORAGE_QUERY_PROPERTY</seealso>
    <seealso cref="STORAGE_PROPERTY_QUERY" />
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.Version">
    <summary>
      <para>Contains the size of this structure, in bytes. The value of this member will change as members are added to
the structure.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.Size">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies the total size of the data returned, in bytes. This may include data that follows this
structure.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.MaximumTokenLifetime">
    <summary>
      <para>The maximum lifetime of the token, in seconds.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.DefaultTokenLifetime">
    <summary>
      <para>The default lifetime of the token, in seconds.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.MaximumTransferSize">
    <summary>
      <para>The maximum transfer size, in bytes.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.OptimalTransferCount">
    <summary>
      <para>The optimal transfer size, in bytes.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.MaximumDataDescriptors">
    <summary>
      <para>The maximum number of data descriptors.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.MaximumTransferLengthPerDescriptor">
    <summary>
      <para>The maximum transfer length, in blocks, per descriptor.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.OptimalTransferLengthPerDescriptor">
    <summary>
      <para>The optimal transfer length per descriptor.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.OptimalTransferLengthGranularity">
    <summary>
      <para>The granularity of the optimal transfer length, in blocks. Transfer lengths that are not an even multiple
of this length may be delayed.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DEVICE_COPY_OFFLOAD_DESCRIPTOR.Reserved">
    <summary>
      <para>Reserved.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>